- Maintaining monetary stability within the framework of the Linked Exchange Rate System;
- Promoting stability and soundness of the financial system (including the banking system);
- Assisting in consolidating Hong Kong's position as an international financial centre, including maintaining and developing Hong Kong’s financial infrastructure; and
- Managing the Exchange Fund.

With the assistance of the Secretary for Financial Services and the Treasury, the Financial Secretary is also responsible for maintaining the stability and soundness of Hong Kong’s financial system and promoting its status as an international financial centre. To implement these policies, the duties of the Financial Management Specialist include:
- Promoting the overall stability and effective operation of the banking system;
- Collaborating with relevant institutions and organizations to develop the debt market;
- Handling matters related to the issuance and circulation of legal tender notes and coins;
- Developing payment, clearance, and settlement systems, and operating relevant systems where appropriate, to promote the safety and efficiency of financial infrastructure; and
- Working with relevant authorities and organizations to foster confidence in Hong Kong’s monetary and financial systems, and to implement appropriate market development measures to enhance Hong Kong’s international competitiveness in financial services.

